Role: Agent A2 (Lead Coder)
Task: Fix Citizens Trait Registration Null Error in PvPBotTrait.java and PvPBotPlugin.java

---

### THE BUG:
When running `/pvpbot spawn`, Citizens throws: `[Citizens] Cannot register a null trait. Was it registered properly?`

---

### CAUSE & RESOLUTION:
1. **Annotation Missing:** The `PvPBotTrait` class in `src/main/java/com/pvpbot/npc/PvPBotTrait.java` is missing the mandatory `@net.citizensnpcs.api.trait.Trait` class-level annotation. Without this, `net.citizensnpcs.api.trait.TraitInfo.of(PvPBotTrait.class)` evaluates to `null`.
   - Update `PvPBotTrait.java` to explicitly add the class-level annotation:
     ```java
     package com.pvpbot.npc;

     @net.citizensnpcs.api.trait.Trait(name = "pvpbot")
     public class PvPBotTrait extends net.citizensnpcs.api.trait.Trait {
         public PvPBotTrait() {
             super("pvpbot");
         }
         // ... rest of your code
     }
     ```

2. **Registry Hook:** Ensure `com/pvpbot/PvPBotPlugin.java` registers the trait properly in `onEnable()`:
   ```java
   net.citizensnpcs.api.CitizensAPI.getTraitFactory().registerTrait(
       net.citizensnpcs.api.trait.TraitInfo.of(PvPBotTrait.class)
   );
   ```

---

### ACTION REQUIRED:
Apply the annotation and verify registration. Run `./build.sh` to ensure a successful compilation, and update the `--- CAC FILE ĐÃ SỬA ---` section in `report.md` cleanly.

Let's fix this null trait issue now!

